caption: Just read anthony ling’s review. Staff laughing without masks on is concerning. I ordered thru uber eats and the call back number on there was wrong. I had to google the information.  This place is listed aa GoGo Chicken on Ubereats.  Food was not that great, i dont know if its because of delivery but some of it came soggy. Bbq skewers had no charcoal taste, they just cover the damn thing on cumin and their blend of spices.

The fish burger is okay but the fried chicken can be better. I don't know if it's the method or the batter they use but it gives the chicken a very different taste than other friend chicken places. Makes it feel 'off'.
omg the squid is sooooo good
Amazing food!! Love it

It takes a while for the food to come out, but I appreciate the freshness of it. The food tastes good however I did notice that some of the staff are laughing outloud and shouting in the kitchen area without masks on. Wait time for side order takes 20+ minutes. Ordering is an issue because they stand behind the counter in the back of the store and you would have to actively attempt to catch their attention. As I wait, I have seen 3 workers come out and smoke in front me and creating a fine mist of lung cancer.
They are quick with taking orders, but it takes a while to get your food because it's made once you order. extremely too salty!! Price is quite high for a quick bite.
Popcorn chicken and squids combo with this Yamy sauce hit the spot so accurate  I am still drooling!
The french fries here are freaking amazing!!!!!!!!!! everything is so crunchy and amazing you won't regret it
Very awesome and the food is so yummy

I've been here four times now thinking the chicken would be better, but it's not. While the prices are reasonable and the food will fill you up, the chicken itself is very dry and unappetizing after a few bites. The wait times are also long for a place that doesn't have too many customers (at the times I went). Will not be coming back for a fifth time.
I SO LOVE THIS PLACE!  I usually come here after the gym & the food is superb.  The staff is very nice & the wait isn't long.
First time here was weeks ago, the wings were good. Ordered a burger, I found it okay. The sauce for the takoyaki was good. Also reasonable prices. Would come back again for fried chicken.

Good food. Got skewers and takoyaki. One of the only places to sell skewers around this area.

(Translated by Google) I am eating chicken here today. The chicken legs he gave me are too small. I told her that I was very happy to give me the second one.  (Original) 今天在这里吃鸡，他给我的鸡腿太小了，我就告诉她，结果就很开心地给了我第二个。

It was okay I can't  give it high marks but prices weren't extremely high but for cost effectiveness for a fast food type outlet and portion size I didn't  feel I got my value for the money. I did notice it was their third anniversary and they had balloons all over the place and thought they were for giving out to children but the guy was making a huge stink about taking them but the way they have them free floating sends the wrong message and  it's  sort of teasing children coming in to eat. I ghink they're a bit much on that and need to relax more if you don't  want  people to take them don't  put them out like that where they're  accessible. Will I come back here? Probably not.  Just thought I'd  try them out since my 4 year old  son  took notice of their balloons but the store was stingy as hell and the food quality and portion size  eh not impressed.  VIVI is way better.
Great food
Surprisingly delicious. If you are looking for an Asian spin on chicken this is a nice go-to. The popcorn chicken is delicious.
One of my favorite place on 86th St. They stive to serve different food there with some popular Taiwanese eats.

I always like to stop by and get their "Braised Pork Over Rice" dish! It's only $5.50 and has rice, braised pork, half an egg, and some green veggies!!! It's so good and the price is definitely right!! I recommend everyone to try this order.
(Translated by Google) Very delicious, eat more and get angry  (Original) 挺好吃，吃多了上火
Tried the big chicken cutlet. Not bad but nowhere close to what I had in HK. Great to have something different in the area.

Great fried chicken for the price. They fry the chicken to order but definitely not fresh chicken.  French fries are seasoned well and thin. I would come here over KFCs but definitely on even grounds with Popeyes
Very unique taste. Nice little place.
Good menu. Portion sizes are fair, and prices are reasonable.
I had the popcorn today.  The chicken was juicy and moist way better than the popcorn chicken from KFC

(Translated by Google) The decoration looks clean and hygienic, the light is a bit soft, there is a food area, the place is not big. There is no recommendation. I would like a No. 1 set. Just eat the freshly fried chicken nuggets like this. Those who like to eat salty will taste it. If it is dipped in sweet and sour plum sauce, you may feel that it has a different flavor, sweet and salty, and salty and sour; French fries are sweet fries , Not potatoes from other stores; fried octopus is not particularly prominent, and the taste is okay; green tea burnt grass is okay. I visited again for the second time and ordered a special set meal and a glass of ice tea. The fried chicken tastes salty and fragrant. It has the flavor and taste of Chinese fried chicken. The preparation method is similar. The French fries are shredded potatoes. When they are first oiled, they are cooked with Chinese five-spice salt and the like. The taste is salty and dipped in tomato sauce, which has a Western flavor. The taste of iced black tea is icy and fragrant. I don't like this taste, but it doesn't mean it is bad. The kitchen products taste good.  (Original) 装修看上去干净卫生，光线有点柔和，有美食享用区，地方并不大。 没有推荐，自己要一份1号套餐。 刚炸的鸡块就这样吃，喜欢吃咸味的会吃出味道，如果沾着甜酸的梅子酱，或许你会觉得别有一番风味，甜中有咸，咸中有酸;薯条是番薯条，并非其他卖场的土豆;炸章鱼没有特别突出，味道还可以;绿茶烧仙草味道可以。 第二次再访，要了一个份特价套餐和一杯冰红茶。 炸鸡味道咸香，有中国炸子鸡的风味和吃法，制作方法差不多。炸薯条是土豆丝，刚上油炉时沁中国五香盐之类，入口咸香，再沾番茄酱别有一番西方风味。冰红茶入口冰爽且香，我不喜欢这种味，但并不代表它不好。 厨房出品味道不错。

I never had grilled chicken this juicy before. Got a Chicken Teriyaki Bento Box the other day and it was straight up no argument the juiciest chicken I've ever had in my life. Haven't tried their other items yet but will visit again.
Yummy chicken and other stuff!
Customer service often takes few minutes, but hey, patience is a virtue.  Food is delicious!

A new take on fried chicken, and finally something different in the area. Great popcorn chicken and nicely seasoned fries. Just avoid the extra long fries - they're just mashed potatoes formed into long sticks.
good junk food

Guys work fast, great taste. Restroom is a little dirty, but at least they have it! Guess if i have a choice, i will pick on this place rather then McDonald's or Burger King. Giving you 5 stars, but make sure to keep it that way! By the way, Chicken is amazing and fresh !!!
Decent chicken burgers and other snacks for a very good price, and it's clean!
Can't really rate it didn't eat here but i can say that this plave seems deader than a graveyard. I tend to steer clear of such places to not get stale food
Unfortunately, the staff doesn't equally welcome their customers. Even though my order would be as simple as a drink, I would be one of the last ones served, even if I came the first.
They have the best popcorn chicken
Nice Taiwanese style chicken

Chicken V is my guilty pleasure. They are a super affordable Asian style fried chicken place that make delicious fries. I am tea not sure what they put in it, but somehow is taste so awesome. I actually don't want to know.

I usually order the combo that comes with fried calamari and popcorn chicken. Flavoring I usually get is garlic. The meal comes with a choice drink of iced tea. It is so good! It comes in a paper bag that you can poke with skewers. Tastewise, I think it is better than vivi's. Pricewise, it is more worth to get the combo than individual orders, since you get to try more variety.  Did I mention that this place delivers?!! Wait time after ordering is ~5-10 minutes so I recommend calling ahead to order then pick up. Otherwise they have seating in the store like a regular restaurant. Food comes piping hot out of the kitchen so it is fresh and crispy.  I highly recommend this place for the food. The drink menu is a little lacking, but this place's focus isn't on the drinks but the food.
Very bad serivce. Taking so long for the order to be served. At least 20 mins. 👎
The food was good and inexpensive, I was pleasantly surprised by the size of the portions.

Initially came here for the chicken. Instead, I opted for the Taiwanese beef noodle soup combo which came with sweet potato fries and salty fried squid legs.  Beef noodle soup was so good that I slurped the bowl clean. The fried squid and fries had a salty taste and crunchy texture which I enjoyed.  Definitely check it out if you're​ looking for something quick to eat.
Great service.
(Translated by Google) Really delicious, with Taiwanese flavor  (Original) 真的好吃，有台湾味
The fried foods here are great.  I love how they have meal combos for a great deal. You can get a combo, which can be shared with 2 people. Love the fried squid and chicken.
